31889), businessman and an unsuccessful candidate for [[Governor of Wisconsin]]<ref name=\"Marquis 1607-1896\">{{cite book | title = Who Was Who in America, Historical Volume, 1607-1896 | publisher = Marquis Who's Who | location = Chicago | year = 1963}}</ref>\n*[[Edward Griffin Beckwith (soldier)|Edward Griffin Beckwith]] (1818\u20131881), soldier and explorer\n*[[Anne Burrell]] (born September 21, 1969), chef and TV personality\n*[[Samuel Northrup Castle]] (1808\u20131894), missionary in Hawaii, founder of Castle & Cooke\n*[[Sarah Brown Ingersoll Cooper]], philanthropist and educator\n*[[John W. Dwinelle]] (1816\u20131888), Lawyer and Politician in California\n*Jane Calkins Egan (1917\u20132009), American Artist, created box assemblages.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://obits.syracuse.com/obituaries/syracuse/obituary.aspx?page=notice&pid=137574648 |title=Jane Calkins Egan Obituary |publisher=Syracuse (NY) Post-Standard |date=December 20, 2009 |accessdate=2014-02-14}}</ref>\n*[[Harrison Stiles Fairchild]] (1820\u20131901), was a Brigadier general in the Union Army\n*[[Siobhan Fallon Hogan|Siobhan Fallon]] (born May 13, 1961), Actress\n*[[Beezie Madden]] (born November 20, 1963), Olympic Equestrian Gold Medalist\n*[[Charles Stebbins]] (1789\u20131873), Acting Lieutenant Governor of New York in 1829, buried at Evergreen Cemetery\n*[[Steve Suhey]] (1922\u20131977), football player at Penn State and in the NFL\n*[[Ezra Greenleaf Weld]] (1801\u20131874), (also known as \"Greenleaf\"), photographer and [[Abolitionism in the United States|abolitionist]]\n*[[Lauren McLean]], [[Boise, Idaho]] politician (raised in Cazenovia)\n*[[Gary Edward Dick Jr.]], [[Washington, DC]] USAF Officer (raised in Cazenovia)\n*Senator Shawn Davis (raised in Cazenovia)\n\n==Economy==\n\n* Caz Equipment Company has its headquarters in Cazenovia.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n* [[GHD Group]] also has one of its headquarters in Cazenovia.\n* [[Marquardt Group]] also has one of its headquarters in Cazenovia.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Cazenovia Village Historic District]]\n* [[Chittenango Falls State Park]]\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nFile:F.H.M Laughlin building.jpg| F.H.M Laughlin building\nFile:Lincklaen House.jpg| Lincklaen_House\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikivoyage|Cazenovia}}\n{{Commons category}}\n\n{{GeoGroup}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080908055906/http://www.cazenoviany.org/ Town of Cazenovia, NY]\n* [http://www.villageofcazenovia.com Village of Cazenovia, NY]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20141030110737/http://caz.cnyric.org/ Cazenovia NY Central Schools]\n* [http://www.cazenovia.com Cazenovia NY Chamber of Commerce]\n* [http://www.cazenovia.edu Cazenovia College]\n* [http://history.rays-place.com/ny/cazenovia-ny.htm  Early history of Cazenovia]\n\n{{Madison County, New York}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Syracuse metropolitan area]]\n[[Category:1793 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Towns in Madison County, New York]]\n[[Category:Cazenovia, New York| ]]\n[[Category:Dutch place names in New York (state)]]\n", "name_user": "1980fast", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNotable people:Phrasing", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cazenovia,_New_York"}
{"title_page": "Azamgarh railway station", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=May 2019}}\n\n{{short description|Railway station in Uttar Pradesh, India}}\n{{distinguish|Azamgarh railway station}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox station\n| name            = Azamgarh Railway Station\n| native_name     =\n| native_name_lang= \n| style           = Indian railway\n| image         = [[File:Indian_Railways_Suburban_Railway_Logo.svg|100px]]\n| image_caption = Indian Railways Logo\n| type            = [[Indian Railway]] station\n| address         = [[Azamgarh]], Uttar Pradesh\n| country         = [[India]]\n| elevation       = 34 m above sea level\n| owned           = \n| operator        = \n| platform        = 3\n| other           = Prepaid Auto cum Taxi Stand\n| structure       = Standard (on ground station)\n| parking         = \n| ADA             = \n| status          = Functioning\n| code            = {{Indian railway code\n  | code = AMH\n  | Station Director = \n  | Area Officer/ AOM = \n  | Zone = NER / North East Railway \n  | Division = Varanasi  \n  }}\n| opened          = \n| closed          = \n| rebuilt         = \n| electrified     = No\n| former          = \n| passengers      = \n| pass_system     = \n| pass_year       = \n| pass_percent    = \n| map_type       = India Uttar Pradesh \n| map_dot_label = \n}}\n'''Azamgarh railway station''' is located in [[Azamgarh]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], India. The Azamgarh railway station lies in the North Eastern railway zone(NER), Gorakhpur under Varanasi division. The station is directly connected to Mau, Delhi, Mumbai, Lucknow, Allahabad, Jabalpur, Nasik, Amritsar, Ludhiana, Ayodhya, Kanpur, Ghaziabad, Etawah and other major & important Indian cities.\n\n{{coord|26.0391|83.1614|type:railwaystation_region:GB|display=title}}Currently it has single line railway route and coming year Azamgarh will have double line railway route with electrification of Mau-Azamgarh-Shahganj rail route. A new rail line from Gorakhpur to Varanasi junction via Azamgarh station is proposed and is under consideration.\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in Azamgarh district]]\n[[Category:Varanasi railway division]]\n\n==IMPORTANT TRAINS of AZAMGARH==\n\n12225 Kaifiyat SF Express\n\n15025 Mau Anand Vihar Express\n\n12226 Kaifiyat SF Express\n\n15026 Anand Vihar Mau Express\n\n11053 Azamgarh weekly Express\n\n11054 Azamgarh weekly Express\n\n13138 Kolkata weekly Express\n\n13137 Azamgarh weekly Express.\n\n==See Also==\n* [[Jaunpur Junction]]\n* [[Kerakat Railway Station]]\n* [[Zafrabad Junction]]\n* [[Mau Junction]]\n\n\n{{UttarPradesh-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=May 2019}}\n\n{{short description|Railway station in Uttar Pradesh, India}}\n{{distinguish|Azamgarh railway station}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2015}}\n\n{{Infobox station\n| name            = Azamgarh Railway Station\n| native_name     =\n| native_name_lang= \n| style           = Indian railway\n| image         = [[File:Indian_Railways_Suburban_Railway_Logo.svg|100px]]\n| image_caption = Indian Railways Logo\n| type            = [[Indian Railway]] station\n| address         = [[Azamgarh]], Uttar Pradesh\n| country         = [[India]]\n| elevation       = 34 m above sea level\n| owned           = \n| operator        = \n| platform        = 3\n| other           = Prepaid Auto cum Taxi Stand\n| structure       = Standard (on ground station)\n| parking         = \n| ADA             = \n| status          = Functioning\n| code            = {{Indian railway code\n  | code = AMH\n  | Station Director = \n  | Area Officer/ AOM = \n  | Zone = NER / North East Railway \n  | Division = Varanasi  \n  }}\n| opened          = \n| closed          = \n| rebuilt         = \n| electrified     = No\n| former          = \n| passengers      = \n| pass_system     = \n| pass_year       = \n| pass_percent    = \n| map_type       = India Uttar Pradesh \n| map_dot_l