tegory:Japanese male actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Japanese male actors]]\n\n{{Japan-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=December 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name                  = Ky\u016b Sazanka\n| image                 = \n| imagesize             = \n| caption               = \n| birthname             = Mineo Suehiro\n| birth_date             = {{Birth date|1914|4|1}}\n| birth_place            = [[Osaka Prefecture|Osaka]], [[Japan]]\n| death_date             = {{Death date and age|1971|3|4|1914|4|1}}\n| death_place            = \n| othername             = \n| occupation            = [[Actor]]\n| yearsactive           = 1932\u20131970\n| spouse                = \n| domesticpartner       = \n| website               = \n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Ky\u016b Sazanka'''|\u5c71\u8336\u82b1 \u7a76|Sazanka Ky\u016b|born April 1, 1914 \u2013 March 4, 1971}} was a Japanese actor.\n\n==Career==\nSazanka debuted as a singer in [[Asakusa]] in 1932 and was active on the vaudeville circuit as a member of the Akireta B\u014dizu.<ref name=kotobank>{{cite web|title=Sazanka Ky\u016b|url=http://kotobank.jp/word/%E5%B1%B1%E8%8C%B6%E8%8A%B1%E7%A9%B6|website=Nihon jinmei daijiten+Plus|publisher=K\u014ddansha|accessdate=29 September 2014}}</ref> He made his film debut in 1946.<ref name=kotobank />\n\n==Selected filmography==\n===Film===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" background: #f9f9f9;\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Role\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Director\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 1955\n| ''[[Meoto zenzai]]'' \n| Ky\u014dichi\n| [[Shir\u014d Toyoda]]\n|-\n| ''[[Takekurabe (1955 film)|Takekurabe]]'' \n| Tatsugor\u014d\n| [[Heinosuke Gosho]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 1956\n| ''[[Mahiru no ankoku]]'' \n| Shiraki\n| [[Tadashi Imai]]\n|-\n| ''[[Koi Sugata Kitsune Goten]]'' \n| Fujimaru\n| [[Nobuo Nakagawa]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 1957\