gory:Japanese male actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Japanese male actors]]\n\n{{Japan-actor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "DDDnfl", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFilm:Added \"Pale Flower\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ky%C5%AB_Sazanka"}
{"title_page": "Peter Kohl", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Peter Kohl\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1965|8|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Ludwigshafen]], [[Rhineland-Palatinate]], [[West Germany]]\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then | death_place   = -->\n<!-- | residence          = {{Unbulleted list|[[London]], UK|[[Zurich]], Switzerland}} -->\n| occupation    = Businessman, entrepreneur and author\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n| father =  [[Helmut Kohl]]\n| mother =  [[Hannelore Kohl]]\n| spouse = [[Elif S\u00f6zen-Kohl]] \n| children = Leyla S\u00f6zen-Kohl\n}}\n'''Peter Kohl''' (born 28 August 1965) is a German businessman and author, who resides in [[Switzerland]]. He is the younger son of former German Chancellor [[Helmut Kohl]] and [[Hannelore Kohl]], and brother of [[Walter Kohl]].   \n\nHe grew up at the family home in [[:de:Ludwigshafen-Oggersheim|Ludwigshafen-Oggersheim]]. Kohl attended the [[Waldorf school]] in [[Ludwigshafen]] and the Liselotte \u2013 Gymnasium (secondary school) across the river in [[Mannheim]]. He was also schooled in the UK and at the Jesuit [[Lyc\u00e9e la Providence]] in Amiens, France. He is a reserve officer and served for two years in the [[Paratrooper Battalion 263 (Bundeswehr)]], now Paratrooper Regiment 26. He holds a BSc. in Economics from [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] (MIT) and a Master\u2019s degree in Economics from the [[University of Vienna]]. \n\nAfter working for 8 years as an investment banker at [[Credit Suisse]] <ref name=PKlautBloomberg>{{cite web|url= https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=11000273&privcapId=10999944|title=Executive Profile, Peter Kohl ... Co-Founder, Lumora Ltd|publisher=Bloomberg L.P.|work=Company Overview of Lumora Ltd|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref> London, and in corporate finance and capital markets at [[Salomon Brothers]], he co-founded an independent corporate finance advisory and fund management firm. While taking a one year sabbatical in 2003, he studied Biotechnology whilst reading for a [[Master of Bioscience Enterprise]] programme at the [[University of Cambridge]]. While at Cambridge, he co-founded, grew and later successfully exited a biotech company. He has lived in London for 17 years. \n\nHis interests include new start-up ventures, technology and fixed income opportunities and has run equity and fund-of-hedge funds. He is an aviation enthusiast and has been a PPL, multi-engine, IFR-rated pilot.\n\nIn May 2001, he married his long-time girlfriend, the Turkish-born banker [[Elif S\u00f6zen-Kohl|Elif S\u00f6zen]], whom he had met in [[Boston]] whilst both were undergraduates at [[MIT]]. She is the daughter of a wealthy industrialist from Istanbul, Dr. Kemal S\u00f6zen, the head of the metal company Kale Kalip Makina Sanayii.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/kohl-swallows-his-words-on-wedding-mission-to-turkey-1.1122443|title=Kohl swallows his words on wedding mission to Turkey|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berliner-zeitung.de/peter-kohl-und-elif-soezen-duerfen-heiraten-der-ex-kanzler-gab-endlich-seinen-segen-16711480|title=Peter Kohl und Elif S\u00f6zen d\u00fcrfen heiraten: Der Ex-Kanzler gab endlich seinen Segen|first=Dilek|last=G\u00fcng\u00f6r|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=PKlautJH/><ref name=\"mittelbayerische\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mittelbayerische.de/politik/helmut-kohls-enkelin-lernt-tuerkisch-20008-art412434.html|title=Helmut Kohls Enkelin lernt T\u00fcrkisch|first=|last=mittelbayerische.de|publisher=}}</ref> Kohl\u2019s wife formerly worked with Goldman Sachs and JP Morgan in London. <ref>Claudia Steiner: \"[http://www.spiegel.de/panorama/christlich-islamische-fusion-kohl-sohn-heiratet-tuerkische-unternehmerstochter-a-136360.html Christlich-islamische Fusion: Kohl-Sohn heiratet t\u00fcrkische Unternehmerstochter],\" ''[[Der Spiegel]]'' 26 May 2001</ref><ref>Dilek G\u00fcng\u00f6r: \"[http://www.berliner-zeitung.de/archiv/peter-kohl-und-elif-soezen-duerfen-heiraten-der-ex-kanzler-gab-endlich-seinen-segen,10810590,9862196.html Peter Kohl und Elif S\u00f6zen d\u00fcrfen heiraten \u2013 Der Ex-Kanzler gab endlich seinen Segen],\" ''[[Berliner Zeitung]]'', 20 December 2000</ref> At the time of their marriage, they had already lived together for over ten years, eight of them in London, most recently in Chelsea.<ref name=\"welt\">{{cite web|url=https://www.welt.de/print-wams/article612253/Ave-Maria-in-Istanbul.html|title=Ave Maria in Istanbul: - WELT|website=DIE WELT}}</ref> She speaks six languages including German. <ref name=\"welt\" /> Reflecting the multicultural nature of the event, the celebration in [[Istanbul]] lasted three days and three marriage ceremonies were involved:  a Roman Catholic marriage, a Muslim marriage and a (Turkish) civil marriage.<ref name=DreifacheHochzeit>{{cite web|url=http://www.mopo.de/dreifache-hochzeit-in-instanbul-mit-500-geladenen-gaesten-kohls-sohn---feier-wie-im-maerchenland-22856044|title=Dreifache Hochzeit in Instanbul mit 500 geladenen G\u00e4sten Kohls Sohn: Feier wie im M\u00e4rchenland |publisher=Morgenpost Verlag GmbH|date=26 May 2001|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref> Noting [[Helmut Kohl|Chancellor Kohl]]'s opposition to admitting [[Turkey]] to the [[European Union]], an [[The Guardian|English newspaper]] asserted excitedly that \"the marriage of Peter Kohl and Elif S\u00f6zen ... [had] the potential to transform German attitudes towards race\".<ref name=PKlautJH>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2000/dec/20/johnhooper|date=20 December 2000|author=[[John Hooper (journalist)|John Hooper]] |title=Kohl's son is to marry a Turk |publisher=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref> \n\nThey have a daughter, Leyla, born in 2002.<ref>\"[http://www.rp-online.de/panorama/huerriyet-helmut-kohl-ist-grossvater-aid-1.2047064 Enkeltochter hei\u00dft Leyla \u2013 'H\u00fcrriyet': Helmut Kohl ist Gro\u00dfvater],\" ''[[Rheinische Post]]'', 12 March 2002</ref> It was reported in 2009 that Leyla had spent time in Turkey to learn Turkish.<ref name=\"mittelbayerische\" /> After the death of Helmut Kohl, Leyla S\u00f6zen-Kohl visited her grandfather's house in Ludwigshafen together with her uncle [[Walter Kohl]] and cousin Johannes Volkmann, but were denied entry to the house by Helmut Kohl's second wife [[Maike Kohl-Richter]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rtlnext.rtl.de/cms/eklat-nach-tod-von-helmut-kohl-sohn-walter-kohl-wird-von-grundstueck-verwiesen-4117594.html|title=Eklat nach Tod von Helmut Kohl: Sohn Walter Kohl wird von Grundst\u00fcck verwiesen|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002 he published a biography of his late mother, co-written with Dona Kujacinski, which received much media attention after her suicide in 2001.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeit.de/2002/10/Die_Perfektionistin/komplettansicht|title=Hannelore Kohl: Die Perfektionistin|author-link=Elisabeth von Thadden|first=Elisabeth|last= von Thadden|date=14 June 2012|publisher=|via=Die Zeit}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.schwaebische.de/home_artikel,-_arid,394024.html|title=Peter Kohl stellt Buch \u00fcber seine Mutter Hannelore Kohl vor|author=dpa newswire}}</ref><ref name=HKlautKSuGB>{{cite web|url=https://www.wr.de/politik/die-leiden-der-hannelore-kohl-id4758742.html|author1=Kirsten Simon|author2=Gregor Boldt|date=13 June 2011|title=Die Leiden der Hannelore Kohl| publisher=Funke Medien NRW GmbH|place= Essen |newspaper=Westf\u00e4lische Rundschau|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* ''Hannelore Kohl.'' Droemer, M\u00fcnchen 2002; second ed.: Knaur, M\u00fcnchen 2013, {{ISBN|978-3-426-78557-7}}.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|35em}}\n\n{{Helmut Kohl}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kohl, Peter}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Helmut Kohl]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Peter Kohl\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1965|8|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Ludwigshafen]], [[Rhineland-Palatinate]], [[West Germany]]\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then | death_place   = -->\n<!-- | residence          = {{Unbulleted list|[[London]], UK|[[Zurich]], Switzerland}} -->\n| occupation    = Businessman, entrepreneur and author\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n| father =  [[Helmut Kohl]]\n| mother =  [[Hannelore Kohl]]\n| spouse = [[Elif S\u00f6zen-Kohl]] \n| children = Leyla S\u00f6zen-Kohl\n}}\n'''Peter Kohl''' (born 28 August 1965) is a German businessman and author, who resides in [[Switzerland]]. He is the younger son of former German Chancellor [[Helmut Kohl]] and [[Hannelore Kohl]], and brother of [[Walter Kohl]].   \n\nHe grew up at the family home in [[:de:Ludwigshafen-Oggersheim|Ludwigshafen-Oggersheim]]. Kohl attended the [[Waldorf school]] in [[Ludwigshafen]] and the Liselotte \u2013 Gymnasium (secondary school) across the river in [[Mannheim]]. He was also schooled in the UK and at the Jesuit [[Lyc\u00e9e la Providence]] in Amiens, France. He is a reserve officer and served for two years in the [[Paratrooper Battalion 263 (Bundeswehr)]], now Paratrooper Regiment 26. He holds a BSc. in Economics from [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] (MIT). He also holds a Master\u2019s degree in Economics from the [[University of Vienna]]. \n\nAfter working for 8 years as an investment banker at [[Credit Suisse]] <ref name=PKlautBloomberg>{{cite web|url= https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=11000273&privcapId=10999944|title=Executive Profile, Peter Kohl ... Co-Founder, Lumora Ltd|publisher=Bloomberg L.P.|work=Company Overview of Lumora Ltd|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref> London, and in corporate finance and capital markets at [[Salomon Brothers]], he co-founded an independent corporate finance advisory and fund management firm. While taking a one year sabbatical in 2003, he studied Biotechnology whilst reading for a [[Master of Bioscience Enterprise]] programme at the [[University of Cambridge]]. While at Cambridge, he co-founded, grew and later successfully exited a biotech company. He has lived in London for 17 years. \n\nHis interests include new start-up ventures, technology and fixed income opportunities and has run equity and fund-of-hedge funds. He is an aviation enthusiast and has been a PPL, multi-engine, IFR-rated pilot.\n\nIn May 2001, he married his long-time girlfriend, the Turkish-born banker [[Elif S\u00f6zen-Kohl|Elif S\u00f6zen]], whom he had met in [[Boston]] whilst both were undergraduates at [[MIT]]. She is the daughter of a wealthy industrialist from Istanbul, Dr. Kemal S\u00f6zen, the head of the metal company Kale Kalip Makina Sanayii.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/kohl-swallows-his-words-on-wedding-mission-to-turkey-1.1122443|title=Kohl swallows his words on wedding mission to Turkey|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berliner-zeitung.de/peter-kohl-und-elif-soezen-duerfen-heiraten-der-ex-kanzler-gab-endlich-seinen-segen-16711480|title=Peter Kohl und Elif S\u00f6zen d\u00fcrfen heiraten: Der Ex-Kanzler gab endlich seinen Segen|first=Dilek|last=G\u00fcng\u00f6r|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=PKlautJH/><ref name=\"mittelbayerische\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mittelbayerische.de/politik/helmut-kohls-enkelin-lernt-tuerkisch-20008-art412434.html|title=Helmut Kohls Enkelin lernt T\u00fcrkisch|first=|last=mittelbayerische.de|publisher=}}</ref> Kohl\u2019s wife formerly worked with Goldman Sachs and JP Morgan in London. <ref>Claudia Steiner: \"[http://www.spiegel.de/panorama/christlich-islamische-fusion-kohl-sohn-heiratet-tuerkische-unternehmerstochter-a-136360.html Christlich-islamische Fusion: Kohl-Sohn heiratet t\u00fcrkische Unternehmerstochter],\" ''[[Der Spiegel]]'' 26 May 2001</ref><ref>Dilek G\u00fcng\u00f6r: \"[http://www.berliner-zeitung.de/archiv/peter-kohl-und-elif-soezen-duerfen-heiraten-der-ex-kanzler-gab-endlich-seinen-segen,10810590,9862196.html Peter Kohl und Elif S\u00f6zen d\u00fcrfen heiraten \u2013 Der Ex-Kanzler gab endlich seinen Segen],\" ''[[Berliner Zeitung]]'', 20 December 2000</ref> At the time of their marriage, they had already lived together for over ten years, eight of them in London, most recently in Chelsea.<ref name=\"welt\">{{cite web|url=https://www.welt.de/print-wams/article612253/Ave-Maria-in-Istanbul.html|title=Ave Maria in Istanbul: - WELT|website=DIE WELT}}</ref> She speaks six languages including German. <ref name=\"welt\" /> Reflecting the multicultural nature of the event, the celebration in [[Istanbul]] lasted three days and three marriage ceremonies were involved:  a Roman Catholic marriage, a Muslim marriage and a (Turkish) civil marriage.<ref name=DreifacheHochzeit>{{cite web|url=http://www.mopo.de/dreifache-hochzeit-in-instanbul-mit-500-geladenen-gaesten-kohls-sohn---feier-wie-im-maerchenland-22856044|title=Dreifache Hochzeit in Instanbul mit 500 geladenen G\u00e4sten Kohls Sohn: Feier wie im M\u00e4rchenland |publisher=Morgenpost Verlag GmbH|date=26 May 2001|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref> Noting [[Helmut Kohl|Chancellor Kohl]]'s opposition to admitting [[Turkey]] to the [[European Union]], an [[The Guardian|English newspaper]] asserted excitedly that \"the marriage of Peter Kohl and Elif S\u00f6zen ... [had] the potential to transform German attitudes towards race\".<ref name=PKlautJH>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2000/dec/20/johnhooper|date=20 December 2000|author=[[John Hooper (journalist)|John Hooper]] |title=Kohl's son is to marry a Turk |publisher=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=21 June 2017}}</ref> \n\nThey have a daughter, Leyla, born in 2002.<ref>\"[http://www.rp-online.de/panorama/huerriyet-helmut-kohl-ist-grossvater-aid-1.2047064 Enkeltochter hei\u00dft Leyla \u2013 'H\u00fcrriyet': Helmut Kohl ist Gro\u00dfvater],\" ''[[Rheinische Post]]'', 12 March 2002</ref> It was reported in 2009 that Leyla had spent time in Turkey to learn Turkish.<ref name=\"mittelbayerische\" /> After the death of Helmut Kohl, Leyla S\u00f6zen-Kohl visited her grandfather's house in Ludwigshafen together with her uncle [[Walter Kohl]] and cousin Johannes Volkmann, but were denied entry to the house by Helmut Kohl's second wife [[Maike Kohl-Richter]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rtlnext.rtl.de/cms/eklat-nach-tod-von-helmut-kohl-sohn-walter-kohl-wird-von-grundstueck-verwiesen-4117594.html|title=Eklat nach Tod von Helmut Kohl: Sohn Walter Kohl wird von Grundst\u00fcck verwiesen|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002 he published a biography of his late mother, co-written with Dona Kujacinski, which received much media attention after her suicide in 2001.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeit.de/2002/10/Die_Perfektionistin/komplettansicht|title=Hannelore Kohl: Die Perfektionistin|author-link=Elisabeth von Thadden|first=Elisabeth|last= von Thadden|date=14 June 2012|publisher=|via=Die Zeit}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.schwaebische.de/home_artikel,-_arid,394024.html|title=Peter Kohl stellt Buch \u00fcber seine Mutter Hannelore Kohl vor|author=dpa newswire}}</ref><ref name=HKlautKSuGB>{{cite web|url=https://www.wr.de/politik/die-leiden-der-hannelore-kohl-id4758742.html|author1=Kirsten Simon|author2=Gregor Boldt|date=13 June 2011|title=Die Leiden der Hannelore Kohl| publisher=Funke Medien NRW GmbH|place= Essen |newspaper=Westf\u00e4lische Rundschau|